abstract: Colbert joked on Thursday that Giuliani “seems more like a Molotov cocktail — used by Russians and full of alcohol.”

abstract: In a palpably tense exchange at an event in South Carolina, Joseph R. Biden Jr. sparred with an organizer protesting Obama-era deportation policies.
snippet: In a palpably tense exchange at an event in South Carolina, Joseph R. Biden Jr. sparred with an organizer protesting Obama-era deportation policies.
lead_paragraph: GREENWOOD, S.C. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and an immigrants’ rights activist on Thursday engaged in an unusually extended clash over Obama-era deportation policies.

lead_paragraph: Two witnesses described their intimate views of an attempted quid pro quo on Thursday, wrapping up a momentous three-day stretch of public hearings. Here’s a recap.

abstract: After two weeks of public testimony, Americans should have a good sense of why an impeachment inquiry was needed.
snippet: After two weeks of public testimony, Americans should have a good sense of why an impeachment inquiry was needed.
lead_paragraph: In his opening statement on Thursday, the last day of the scheduled public hearings in the House’s impeachment inquiry, Devin Nunes, the top Republican on the House Intelligence Committee, expressed his hope that “today’s hearing marks the merciful end of this spectacle in the impeachment committee.”

abstract: China’s anger, Benjamin Netanyahu, royal scandals: Here’s what you need to know.
snippet: China’s anger, Benjamin Netanyahu, royal scandals: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: Officials in Beijing are furious over a U.S. bill compelling the government to support Hong Kong protesters. Passed by Congress this week, it awaits President Trump’s signature.

abstract: In events across Atlanta, Ms. Warren, Bernie Sanders and others described how they would address the concerns and priorities of black voters.
snippet: In events across Atlanta, Ms. Warren, Bernie Sanders and others described how they would address the concerns and priorities of black voters.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — One day after a televised debate featuring significant exchanges about race, Democratic presidential candidates fanned out across this capital of black political power to pitch their message to black voters and send a clear signal: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. should not take support from African-Americans for granted.

headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Makes Pitch to Black Women In Speech About Racial Inequities
headline_print_headline: Taking Debate Theme Outside Arena in a Bid To Earn Black Support
byline_original: By Astead W. Herndon and Thomas Kaplan

abstract: No Democrat in modern times has won the party’s nomination without claiming majorities of black voters, the most crucial voting bloc in South Carolina and an array of delegate-rich states.
snippet: No Democrat in modern times has won the party’s nomination without claiming majorities of black voters, the most crucial voting bloc in South Carolina and an array of delegate-rich states.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has 154 endorsements from current or former black or Hispanic elected officials. Senator Kamala Harris has 93. Senator Bernie Sanders has 91. Senator Cory Booker has 50. Senator Elizabeth Warren has 43.
